data.current_description:
If you are interested in a list of channels that have had there schedule updated you can filter by the following query params.
 - scheduleStart
 - scheduleEnd
 - scheduleUpdatedSince

adding these query params will filter the channel collection to only return channels that have been updated within the given range, updatedSince stores the state of your previous call.

Example Usage: Every 10 minutes get me the channels that have updated schedules for the next 2 weeks.

/channel?platform={uuid}&scheduleStart={today}&scheduleEnd={today + 2 weeks}&updatedSince={10 minutes ago}

Also please note epg numbers are only exposed when a platform and region are passed to the query.
data.summary_suggestion: Retrieve channels with optional schedule filters
data.description_suggestion: Retrieves a collection of TV channels with optional filtering by schedule date range and update timestamp. Supports incremental updates via the scheduleUpdatedSince parameter to track changes since the last call. Query parameters: scheduleStart (filter channels with schedules after this date), scheduleEnd (filter channels with schedules before this date), scheduleUpdatedSince (return only channels updated after this timestamp). Note: EPG numbers are only included when both platform and region parameters are provided. Returns an array of channel objects matching the specified filters.
data.reasoning: Original summary 'Channel Collection' is too generic and doesn't indicate the filtering capability. Description has grammatical errors ('there' should be 'their') and unclear structure. Improved version clarifies the filtering parameters, explains the incremental update pattern, specifies what EPG exposure depends on, and explicitly states the return type for better AI agent understanding.
